= render partial: 'problem_header'
%p
  The Tic Tac Toe company is expanding into Mazes! They need help making sure that their mazes will be solvable for Kids!
  Your task is to go from the top left corner of the maze to the bottom right hand corner and print out the directions! 
  There are no loops in the mazes.
%p
  Return the directions you took while travelling the maze, or -1 if the maze is impossible.

%h2 Sample Problem
%h4 Input
.data
  = link_to 'Download Sample Maze', '/mazes/sample.txt'  

%br

%h4 Solution
.data
  %code
    1E 1E 1S 1S 1E 1E 1S 1W 1S 1E
%h4
  NOTE: one square in the maze is not perfectly equivalent to a single character. 
%br

%h2 Actual Problem
.data
  - number = @prob[:phrase]

  - maze_names =  ['OOOOXXOO','XOOOXXXX','OOOXXOOX','OOOOXXXX','XOOOXOOO','OXXXOOXX','XOXXXXOX','OXXOXXOX','OOXOOOOX','OXOOXXOO', 'OXXOXXXX', 'XXOXOOXO', 'OXXOXXOO', 'XOXOXXOX', 'OXOXXXOX', 'XOXOOOXO', 'XXOOXXOX', 'OXXOXXXO', 'OXOOOXOO', 'OXXOOXXX' ]
  = link_to 'Download Maze', '/mazes/'+maze_names[Integer(number)]+'.txt'
    

